<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870730-0025 </DOCNO><HL> GE's RCA Unit GetsNavy Engineering JobTotalling $42.4 Million</HL><DD> 07/30/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GE ROK HON LIT GM GMH SMF WX UTXDEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   RCA Corp., a unit of General Electric Co., received a $42.4 million Navy contract for engineering services for the Aegis shipbuilding program.    Rockwell International Corp. received Air Force contracts totaling $38.3 million for B-1B aircraft engineering services and test equipment.    Honeywell Inc. got a $34.1 million Air Force contract for communications equipment.    Litton Industries Inc. was issued a $22.3 million Army contract for position-determining systems.    Engineered Air Systems Inc. received a $19 million Army contract for welding machines and equipment.    Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of General Motors Corp., won Air Force contracts totaling $16.1 million for radio equipment and manufacturing-plant improvements.    Westinghouse Electric Corp. was awarded a $14.1 million Navy contract for submarine-launched ballistic-missile equipment for England.    Pratt andamp; Whitney, a unit of United Technologies Corp., received Navy contracts totaling $13.2 million for F-404 and J-52 aircraft engine parts.    Singer Co. said its Librascope division unit received a $10 million Navy contract for shipboard satellite communications equipment. </TEXT></DOC>